<p>A closure is created when the inner function is somehow made available to any scope outside the outer function.</p>

<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>

<pre><code>var outer = function(params){ //Outer function defines a variable called params
    var inner = function(){ // Inner function has access to the params variable of the outer function
        return params;
    }
    return inner; //Return inner function exposing it to outer scope
},
myFunc = outer("myParams");
myFunc(); //Returns "myParams"
</code></pre>
